Etymology[edit]

From vōx (“voice”) + facio (“do, make, produce”)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /woːˈki.fi.koː/, [woːˈkɪ.fɪ.koː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /voˈt͡ʃi.fi.ko/, [vɔˈt͡ʃiː.fi.kɔ]

Verb[edit]

vōcificō (present infinitive vōcificāre, perfect active vōcificāvī, supine vōcificātum); first conjugation

  1. I cry aloud, utter a loud cry; proclaim
